Gold Trades Near Record on Demand for Haven Amid Turmoil in Middle East

-- B y   W e n d y   P u g h
-- 
2011-03-02T23:11:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/gold-trades-near-record-on-demand-for-haven-amid-turmoil-in-middle-east.html
Gold for immediate delivery rose 0.1
percent to trade near a record reached yesterday on demand for a
haven. The metal was at $1,435.45 an ounce at 10:02 a.m.
Melbourne time, compared with the all-time high of $1,440.32.  Bullion for April delivery in  New York  fell 0.2 percent to
$1,435.50 an ounce after reaching a record yesterday of $1,441.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Pugh in Melbourne at 
